    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - NOZZLES - CLEANING, COMPONENT INSPECTION AND REPAIR</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CLEANING, COMPONENT INSPECTION AND REPAIR</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CLEANING</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all parts in a suitable cleaning agent.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>DO NOT intermix nozzle valves. Keep each valve with its original nozzle body.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Soak nozzle valve (tip) in a varnish removing cleaning agent.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Probe all nozzle spray holes with the appropriate size cleaning needle found in
                    <emph type="bold">SE-2202</emph>
                    nozzle cleaning kit.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The needle used must be smaller in diameter than nozzle spray hole. See nozzle chart for
                            number and size of orifice holes.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean all ducts and nozzle spray holes with filtered compressed air.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thoroughly clean interior of nozzle cap nut. All carbon deposits must be removed (soak
                    to loosen - brass brush to clean).
